it is critical that counselors are well-prepared to advance learning and development, informed by a strong commitment and paradigmatic orientation to social justice. through our faculty-led study abroad programs, students learn about and reflect on issues of community and cultural development, international and cross-cultural issues, sustainability (environmental, social, political, and economic), community development and human service, and human rights and citizenship education. learn more about our recent study abroad course below.this program featured a partnership with the u.n-mandated university for peace (upeace), located in san jose, costa rica. upeace was established in december 1980 as a treaty organization by the un general assembly. upeace's mission is: to provide humanity with an international institution of higher education for peace with the aim of promoting among all human beings the spirit of understanding, tolerance and peaceful coexistence, to stimulate cooperation among peoples and to help lessen obstacles and threats to world peace and progress, in keeping with the noble aspirations proclaimed in the charter of the united nations.this course utilized inquiry-based and seminar-style learning experiences. in addition to the program leaders, studentshad opportunities to learn from distinguished international and local guest speakers and facilitators in classroom settings at the upeace campus and on guided tours and site visits.other program years in costa rica included: 2012, 2013, 2014, 2105, and 2018. check out some of the pictures below.class at the university for peaceschool in la carpiomonteverde cloud forrest reserveupeace outdoor group activitytarcoles sustainable fishing villagela carpiospice farmdowntown san jose, costa ricauniversity for peace (upeace) monumentnacientes palmichaluniversity for peace (upeace) monumentnacientes palmichalbutterfly farmpainting homes with the kids in la carpiola carpio - picture with kids and painted trash di